                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340904-229-victim1357 t18340904-229-viclabel1287"></join> in <placeName id="t18340904-229-crimeloc1288">Berwick-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18340904-229-crimeloc1288" type="placeName" value="Berwick-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18340904-229-crimeloc1288" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340904-229-off1285 t18340904-229-crimeloc1288"></join>. On the 22nd of September the prisoner came to the shop - I knew her before, and watched her - I saw her go up to a shawl, and unpin it - she went to a partition in the shop, returned, and took another pin out - she returned a third time, and took the shawl down and retired again - and the fourth time, she went and took a pin out of another shawl - two gentlemen came in to purchase a gun, and then she went out - I pursued, and overtook her six yards off, and found the shawl on her.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Are you sure you saw all this? A. Yes; she has pawned at our house to the amount of 3l. or 4l., I should think.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I found the shawl on the ground when I went in - I have been in the habit of going there for nine years - he has got a great deal of my property in his house.</p>
